Package: pft
Type: Package
Title: Compute ATS-Compliant PFT Reference Values
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Pat",   family = "Johnson",   email = "johnson.pat@mayo.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8365-1375")),
    person(given = "Zach",  family = "Quicksall",
           role = "aut"),
    person(given = "Jairo", family = "Pena",
           role = "aut")
    )
Description: Computes predicted values and lower/upper limits of normal
    for pulmonary function tests according to American Thoracic Society
    and European Respiratory Society reference standards. Supports
    spirometry (GLI 2012 and the race-neutral GLI 2022 / "GLI Global"
    equations), static lung volumes (GLI 2021), and the carbon monoxide
    transfer factor / diffusion capacity (GLI 2017 TLCO, including the
    2020 author correction). Also assigns ATS/ERS interpretive
    pattern labels (Normal, Non-specific, Obstructed, Restricted, Mixed)
    from spirometry and lung-volume measurements following the
    interpretation algorithm in Stanojevic et al. ERJ 2022.
